# Discord watch

- DOM selectors live **only** in `extension/domains/discord/content/selectors.ts` â€” bump `SELECTOR_VERSION` after manual verification.
- Bootstrap quiet period (`MESSAGE_BOOTSTRAP_QUIET_MS`) prevents historical links opening on page load.
- Empty allowlist = observe only; `process-links` no-ops.
- Own messages are skipped (`isOwnMessage` in extract/session).
- Thread URLs share parent channel allowlist (`parseChannelId` uses parent segment).
- Prefer visible message `textContent` URLs over Discord redirect `href`s.
- Side panel domain + keyword/SKU editor is Discord-surface only; settings debounce 400ms via `useChannelDiscordSettings`.
- Per-channel positive/negative keywords gate auto-open when SKU open mode is off (`shouldOpenByKeywords`); skipped links use history kind `keyword_skipped`.
- Global **SKU open mode** uses `messageScanRoot` extraction and `decideSkuOpenAction` in handlers; per-channel `watch_skus.target`; opens constructed Target PDP; history kind `sku_skipped`.
- When per-channel **Auto ATC** is enabled, Target product links open via `openTargetLinkRepeated` in core `open-product-link.ts` (repeat count from global `retailer_link_open_count`, default 1; Auto ATC path handled internally); other allowlisted links open via `openPassiveProductLink` in a new window or background tab per global `open_links_in_window` setting (default on).

See `extension/domains/discord/AGENTS.md`.
